’Щ@6bdb9ece25cb52c0c3c002b4800d92421c1c838300d648266c8fe487b312bfb0ЪVTitle: title: str length
Path: Examples
Content:
Return the lengths of a string in bytes.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'hello' | str length
5

```
Count length of a string in grapheme clusters.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'рҹҮҜрҹҮөгҒ»гҒ’ гҒөгҒҢ гҒҙгӮҲ' | str length  --grapheme-clusters
9

```
Return the lengths of multiple strings in bytes.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ['hi' 'there'] | str length
в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ 0 в”Ӯ 2 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1 в”Ӯ 5 в”Ӯ
в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ


```
Return the lengths of a string in chars.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'hГӨllo' | str length --chars
5

```
